{
  "stem": "1918.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When she saw that group, and she knew that we were safe in another barrack, then she would take her pitcher and hand it over to the girl so that she would look like one because she still had the white kerchief, and she could look like one who is working in the unterkunft, therefore she's not with the group that's going to the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she saved people innumerable times like that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was such humanity.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Or I remember, on one occasion in the second camp, where there was no crematorium to burn the dead, so we actually had to bury them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the group was selected.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The-- the-- the-- a number of were selected on this one occasion to bury a girl who died.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was selected as one to carry the body, one out of four or five.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And my sister Chica was selected as one who would dig the grave.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The frozen earth.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she knew that I was much more afraid of a dead body than she was.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That I was terrified.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That I was really just a child in my heart, a terror-stricken child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she had such empathy that she whispered to me, and she said, I could not change places with her and not carry the body.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But she was able to pretend that she's walking along, and she whispered to me, and she said, I put my-- I'll put my hand under the body, and you put your hand on mine.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So I didn't feel the cold body.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Such exquisite humanity that you have experienced.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was my sister, but there are countless stories like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
